{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-entry-js","path":"/notes/py/socket/recv","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"socket.recv"},"html":"<h3><code class=\"language-text\">socket.recv(bufsize, flag)</code></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>This function receives data from a socket</li>\n<li>This refers to a client or server receiving data from the other</li>\n<li>The <code class=\"language-text\">bufsize</code> limits how much data can be received</li>\n<li>For example, <code class=\"language-text\">socket.recv(1024)</code> will read at most 1024 bytes</li>\n<li>It will block I/O if no data has arrived</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Example of <code class=\"language-text\">recv</code></h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\"><span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> socket\n\n<span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> sock <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> socket<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>AF_INET<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> SOCK_STREAM<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> address <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">''</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">25000</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> sock<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>bind<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>address<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> client<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> ad <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> sock<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>accept<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> data <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> client<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>recv<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">100</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>data<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token string\">'hello world'</span>  <span class=\"token comment\"># client sent 'hello world' beforehand</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>References</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://index-of.co.uk/Python/Python%20Essential%20Reference,%20Fourth%20Edition.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Python Essential Reference</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Documentation for socket API</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.arp.com/medias/13916546.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Python in a Nutshell</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/7180671/12777044\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Is Receiving Data a Blocking Call?</a></li>\n</ul>"}},"pageContext":{"slug":"py/socket/recv","previousSlug":"py/socket/makefile","nextSlug":"py/socket/recvfrom","previousTitle":"socket.makefile","nextTitle":"socket.recvfrom"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}